comment.shortText: Defines an interface that represents a single chat message in a conversation with an AI.
The name of the author of the message.
comment.text: This is required if the role is `function`.

comment.shortText: The contents of the message.
The reason why the message was finished.
The role of the message.
comment.text:
- `system` means that the message was generated by the system. Useful for telling the AI how to behave while.
- `user` means that the message was generated by the user.
- `assistant` means that the message was generated by the AI assistant.
- `function` means that the message contains the results of a function call.

Defines an interface that represents options for [`ai.chat(message, options)`](ref:ai.chat-string).

tags.text: Types that are used in AI actions.

comment.shortText: The HTTP endpoint that the request should interface with.
The frequency penalty.
comment.text: Positive values penalize new tokens based on their existing frequency in the text so far, decreasing the model's likelihood to repeat the same line verbatim.

comment.shortText: The model that should be used.
comment.text:
If not specified, then a default will be used.

Currently, the following models are supported:

- `gpt-4`
- `gpt-3.5-turbo`

comment.shortText: The presence penalty.
comment.text: Positive values penalize new tokens based on whether they appear in the text so far, increasing the model's likelihood to talk about new topics.

comment.shortText: The temperature that should be used.
comment.text: If not specified, then a default will be used.

comment.shortText: The nucleus sampling probability.
Defines an interface that represents options for {@link ai.chat-string}.
